Key Match Events: Abdel Samad Ezzalzouli opened the scoring for Morocco in the 18th minute.
Azzedine Ounahi scored a stunning strike from outside the box in the 38th minute.
Azzedine Ounahi scored his second goal in first-half stoppage time.
Achraf Hakimi scored in the 45th minute.
Soufiane Rahimi converted a penalty in the 71st minute.
Morocco's goalkeeper Yassine Bounou exited prematurely due to a hamstring strain.
Post-Match Reflections: Head coach Walid Regragui aims to improve the national team’s overall performance despite criticisms.
Regragui seeks to address the team’s struggles against opponents employing a deep defensive block.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was officiated by Gambian referee Bakary Gassama, assisted by Abdoulie Bojang Jallow and Nfally Jarju, with Omar Salah as the fourth official.
